text: Harry Moy (1911-1994) was a boxer who competed for England. ==Boxing career== Moy won a bronze medal in the lightweight division at the 1934 British Empire Games in London. ==Personal life== He lived in Camberwell. ==References== Category:1911 births Category:1994 deaths Category:English male boxers Category:Commonwealth Games bronze medallists for England Category:Commonwealth Games medallists in boxing Category:Boxers at the 1934 British Empire Games Category:Lightweight boxers
